entry.title: Climate Funding Gets Squeezed by Volatile Markets
entry.content: The interest-rate increases and market volatility that hit risky investments last year have finally caught up with green startups.

entry.title: They Dreamed of Living by the Sea. One Problem: Their Home Was in the English Countryside
entry.content: Annie Heyworth and Tim Healy didn’t want to move from Gloucestershire to be on the water, so they dug up a 6-foot-deep pond while building their roughly 2,400-square-foot timber house.

entry.title: 'Bridesmaids' Star Chris O'Dowd Wants to Know Why His Fridge Has Wi-Fi
entry.content: In ‘The Big Door Prize,’ the new series from a ‘Schitt’s Creek’ writer, the actor plays an everyman in an odd situation. Here, he talks about cauliflower nachos, sleeping like ‘garbage’ and pushing his dog in a pram.
